snippet.title: Jumpstart Explorers Full Playthrough
snippet.description:
Jumpstart Explorers Full Playthrough

Jumpstart Explorers is a game released by Knowledge Adventure in 2001. It focuses on history concepts for ages 5-8.

In this game, CJ's six nieces and nephews have used his time machine to play hide-and-seek in time. Now CJ and Edison must search through several points in history to find them.

The player can earn points by playing activities, which can be traded in for stickers. There are forty stickers to collect. The player can also earn rainy day crafts each time they find a tadpole. There are twenty-five rainy day crafts to collect.

The game has three difficulty levels. The player chooses their difficulty level when they start a new game, and they can change their difficulty level at the sign-in screen.
